record.text: And then Seligman (1999), Zlotnick (2001) etc but the bulk of the evidence really did not appear before 2010, probably because before 2010s we really didn't have ways to work on a large number of subthreshold people.

There were a few studies in 1980s, including Tableman  (1987) and Vega (1987). HOWEVER, when we limited ourselves to prevention studies that actually used formal diagnostic criteria, the earliest trials seem to be: Munoz (1995) and Clarke (1995).

In 1984 a report by the US National Institute of Mental Health concluded that prevention of depression is impossible.
(Lobel B, Hirschfeld RM. Depression: what we know (DHHS publication no.ADM 84-1318). Rockville, MD: National Institute of Mental Health, 1984.)

今の詩(雑な括り)には、他なる言葉を言葉の中に招き入れるような、あるいは他なる場所で書くような、他になってしまうような、そういう詩が求められているように思う。多和田葉子とかテレサ・ハッキョン・チャのような。実際それは1つの豊かな可能性だ。でも二十億光年の(それは途方に暮れるような)孤独の中で日本語の中に立ち尽くした詩人が、日本語の中でなお孤独であったところに、〈国民詩人〉なる称はあるんじゃないか(そしてその称は、谷川俊太郎に冠せられて終わるのではないか……)
